### Smoke / Manual API checks for local docker-compose environment
### Usage:
### 1. Start the stack: `make env-smoke-up`
### 2. Register the user below, then create a KB:
###    `make env-smoke-create-kb ARGS="--username smoke_manual_001"`
### 3. Copy the printed `kb_id` into `@kbId`
### 3. Run requests top-to-bottom in REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@username = smoke_manual
@email = smoke_manual@example.com
@password = Password123
@kbId = 019dbade-5aec-1204-03db-8d58f3ca621e


### Health - live
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health_check/live
Accept: application/json


### Health - ready
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health_check/db_ready
Accept: application/json


### Auth - register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "confirm_password": "{{password}}"
}


###
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username={{username}}&password={{password}}


### Users - current user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json


### Knowledge - upload stream
### Note: replace `@kbId` with a real knowledge base ID before running.
### If you do not have one yet, create/seed one first, or use the smoke pytest
### that seeds a KB automatically.
###
# @name uploadStream
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/knowledge/bases/{{kbId}}/upload-stream
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=SmokeBoundary

--SmokeBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="demo.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

hello knowledge upload
this file is for manual smoke verification
--SmokeBoundary--


### Knowledge - task status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/knowledge/tasks/{{uploadStream.response.body.$.task_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json


### Knowledge - file status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/knowledge/files/{{uploadStream.response.body.$.file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json
